
[1]hydropical

   HYDROP'ICAL, a. [L. hydrops; Gr. dropsy; water.]

   1. Dropsical; diseased with extravasated water.

   2. Containing water; caused by extravasated water; as a hydropic
   swelling.

   3. Resembling dropsy.

   Every lust is a kind of hydropic distemper, and the more we drink the
   more we shall thirst.
